<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
All specimens studied have separated prefrontals and parietals in contact, except the 
<typeStatus box="[264,366,1084,1110]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
which has prefrontals in contact and parietals barely in point­contact. Seven specimens have four supraoculars on both sides, two specimens have five supraoculars on the right and four on the left side, and one specimen has five supraoculars on the right and three on the left side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,284,1830]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
All specimens from 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" box="[565,655,1244,1270]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">AMNH</collectionCode>
