<collectionCode box="[722,813,1244,1270]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/ra64-3eva" name="University of Michigan, Museum of Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">UMMZ</collectionCode>
are lighter in coloration than those from 
<collectionCode box="[264,365,1284,1310]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/fxnk-ibav" name="Universidad de los Andes, Laboratorio de Biogeografia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">ULABG</collectionCode>
, with cream clear venter. This difference seems to result from a difference in fixation conditions. The single juvenile (
<collectionCode box="[699,792,1324,1350]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/ra64-3eva" name="University of Michigan, Museum of Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">UMMZ</collectionCode>
<number box="[800,875,1324,1350]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="57435.0">57435</number>
) has a more contrasted and vivid coloration than the adults. Of the eight adult specimens, four have a dark dot on each fourth supraocular. Position of the dorsal scale where the thin dark vertebral stripe begins: 
<number box="[1278,1323,1404,1430]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
